I went here for a happy hour with a friend based on the Yelp reviews that I read.
I was excited for a nice wine bar near my work and it looked like it had a great happy hour menu.
I opted to have wine, and since I had a ways to drive home, I just went for a glass.
If you had a larger group or were within walking distance, they have wine by the bottle and at happy hour, the 2nd bottle is $1!
We opted to sample 3 of the appetizers.
We tried the Peppy Dew Peppers, Wild Mushroom Bruschetta, and the Chef's Board.
Everything was delicious.
I expected the bread on the  bruschetta to be more crunchy/grilled, but it was tasty nonetheless.
We sat outside but it was a little bright with no shade to block the setting sun.
Looks like they've planted trees to help, but in the mean time, they might consider a screen/shade for that are.
Some misters would go a long was as it starts to warm up as well.
All in all, I would definitely go back and happy hour there again.

