My boyfriend and I ordered burgers.
I had the sun devil with the Salut fries and my boyfriend had the Salut Burger with the Greek Salad.
Both of us REALLY enjoyed our meals.
The buns were nice and light and soft and the chipotle aioli that came on the sun devil was delicious!
It was creamy with just enough kick not to overwhelm everything.
Because our groupon came with 2 cocktails, we were able to venture out and try a couple drinks we might not have tried (they are a little expensive- about $10 avg, but you do get a pretty big glass, so I suppose it evens out).
I had the house margarita and it was very smooth, and super delicious.
They sweeten it with agave nectar and add a couple limes.
It was a great combination.
My boyfriend had an orange/rum cocktail called the Dark & Stormy, and he liked it so much he had 2!
I think it had a dark rum and ginger beer and a couple of other things in it.
Like I said earlier, the ambiance is wonderful, and our server was very nice.
The only reason I docked off one star is because the chairs on the patio were a bit uncomfortable and the menu layout was a little confusing (it took us a bit to find what we were looking for, and a lot of things are on separate sheets of laminated paper).
